dpul.title: DPUL should not load the manifest from figgy when enqueuing a ReindexExhibitJob
Reindexing Slavic items is throwing a "405 Not Allowed"

comments.body: If this collection won't index it will impact the index migration that we've scheduled for Monday.
Changed urgency to ASAP. See @hackartisan  above and now 0 items have indexed for the site.

I found a 499 in the logs from this request. https://app.datadoghq.com/logs?query=service%3A%28dpul%20OR%20nginxplus%20OR%20figgy%20OR%20solr%29&context_event=AQAAAX612zbI9nBRNQAAAABBWDYxMnpiYkFBQkk5R2xxamU3RUd3QmY&event=&index=&stream_sort=desc&viz=&from_ts=1643728547853&to_ts=1643728548454&live=false

I'm not sure how that ended up showing as a 405. But this is an nginx error screen, not a rails error screen, which suggests that the problem happened between servers rather than in the application.

I have clicked reindex again and did not receive an error. There is a lot in the queue, though, so it will be a while.

Here's the story from more logs examination:

- the load balancer sent the request to dpul, waited around for a response
- nginx on the dpul machine received the request, routed, it, and waited for rails to respond
- the app started fetching the manifest from figgy
- nginx on the dpul machine didn't get a response quickly enough, and returned a 499
- the load balancer served a 405 error (still not sure why a 405)
- the app got the manifest and enqueued the job, returning a 302 redirect to... nobody because the nginx service wasn't really listening anymore

The job was enqueued at 9:15, 10:15, and 12:02. 2 of them are still on the queue but one was performed between 11:07 and 11:45 (ironically right before the last one was enqueued).

Deduplicate role inclusion for molecule testing?

comments.body:
At the level of an individual role, refactoring the way we maintain role dependencies will require:

For each role dependency we remove from the `meta/main.yml` file of Role A:
- [ ] ensure the README for Role A lists the dependency
- [ ] add the dependency to the `molecule/default/converge.yml` file for Role A, so it runs in tests
- [ ] add the dependency to every playbook that runs Role A
- [ ] until all roles are converted, add the dependency to `meta/main.yml` for any other role that lists Role A as a dependency, and to any playbooks that run those roles
